org.csdgn.amf3

Class AmfArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfValue
      • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfArray

  • public class AmfArray
extends AmfValue
    Associated with the AMF true and false types. Unlike a standard array in Java, an AmfArray has both a Dense (List like) portion and an Associative (Map like) portion. This class handles both of these.
    Author:
    Robert Maupin

      • remove

        public AmfValue remove(java.lang.String key)
        Removes the mapping for a key from the associated part of this AmfArray if it is present. More formally, if this it contains a mapping from key k to value v such that (key==null ? k==null : key.equals(k)), that mapping is removed.
        Parameters:
        key - key whose mapping is to be removed from the map
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with key, or null if there was no mapping for key.
